Autopsy: forensics open-source tool
-analyze mobile devices and digital media
-used in law enforcement, national security, litigation support and corp investigation

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Installation:
https://www.autopsy.com/download

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Workflow overview
-Basic workflow
1. Create case for data source = new case
2. Select data source to analyze
3. congi the ingest modules to extract specific artifacts
4. Review artifacts extracted by the ingest modules
5. Create Report

-autopsy files extension: .aut

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Data Sources
-Disk image or vm file
-documentation: http://sleuthkit.org/autopsy/docs/user-docs/4.12.0/ds_page.html
Raw Single (For example: *.img, *.dd, *.raw, *.bin)
Raw Split (For example: *.001, *.002, *.aa, *.ab, etc)
EnCase (For example: *.e01, *.e02, etc)
Virtual Machines (For example: *.vmdk, *.vhd)

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Ingest Modules
-Autopsy plug-ins
-configure ingest modules
-some ingest modules have pre-run settings and some do not

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

User interface
-Tree Viewer (Left Pane)
Data Sources - all the data will be organized as you would typically see it in a normal Windows File Explorer. 
Views - files will be organized based on file types, MIME types, file size, etc. 
Results - as mentioned earlier, this is where the results from Ingest Modules will appear. 
Tags - will display files and/or results that have been tagged (read more about tagging here)
Reports - will display reports either generated by modules or the analyst. (read more about reporting here)


-Result Viewer (Top right pane)
Notice that the Result Viewer pane has 3 tabs: Table, Thumbnail, and Summary.


-Keyword Search (Upper Top Right)
AD-HOC keyword search


-Contents Viewer (Bottom right pane)
-Score, Comment, Occurrence

-Status Area (Lower Bottom right)
Progress bar for ingest modules progress 

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


Visualization Tools
-Images/videos
-communications
-Timeline
